---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'How to Choose the Right Stairlift for Your NY Home | Buying Guide';
const description = 'Straight vs curved stairlifts, indoor vs outdoor, features to consider for homes in Rochester, Buffalo, and Syracuse NY. Expert advice from local mobility specialists.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">How to Choose the Right Stairlift</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">A practical guide for homeowners in Western and Central New York.</p>

    <div class="prose prose-slate">
      <h2>1. Straight vs Curved Stairlifts</h2>
      <p>Most homes in newer suburbs (e.g., around Rochester or Syracuse) have straight stairs and can use simpler, lower-cost straight models. Historic homes in Buffalo’s Elmwood Village or Rochester’s Park Avenue often require custom curved rails that follow the staircase shape.</p>

      <h2>2. Indoor vs Outdoor Models</h2>
      <p>Outdoor stairlifts are built to withstand snow, ice, and rain — essential for Upstate NY winters. They include weatherproof covers and heated options.</p>

      <h2>3. Key Features to Consider</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Swivel seat for safe transfer at the top</li>
        <li>Folding rails and seats for narrow hallways</li>
        <li>Battery backup (critical during power outages common in winter storms)</li>
        <li>Weight capacity (standard 300 lbs, heavy-duty up to 400+ lbs)</li>
        <li>Remote controls and app integration for modern homes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Next Steps for Your Home</h2>
      <p>The best way to choose is with a free in-home assessment. Our team measures your specific staircase in Rochester, Buffalo, or Syracuse and recommends the best model for your needs and budget.</p>

      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block mt-4 bg-sky-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl">Schedule Your Free Assessment →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
